article.headline: Meadow's 12 help Boise State knock off VCU 65-61

images.name: Toibu Lawal gets up for the beautiful flush
images.caption: Toibu Lawal gets up for the beautiful flush

article.linkText: Meadow's 12 help Boise State knock off VCU 65-61
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. -- — Andrew Meadow scored 12 points as Boise State beat VCU 65-61 on Friday night in the ESPN Events Invitational. Meadow shot 5 for 10, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc for the Broncos (3-2). Tyson Degenhart scored 10 points and Cam Martin finished with eight points. Max Shulga led the way for the Rams (3-3) with 24 points and eight rebounds. VCU also got 14 points and nine rebounds from Toibu Lawal. In addition, Zeb Jackson finished with eight points, six rebounds and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
